1
00:00:41,250 --> 00:00:42,041
Uh...

2
00:00:42,750 --> 00:00:44,125
Excuse me, who are you—

3
00:00:51,500 --> 00:00:52,291
Hello.

4
00:00:53,208 --> 00:00:54,791
This is my room.

5
00:00:54,833 --> 00:00:55,916
Excuse me, who are you?

6
00:00:58,333 --> 00:00:59,125
Ah.

7
00:01:00,083 --> 00:01:01,250
Hold on a sec.

8
00:01:01,250 --> 00:01:02,291
I'll be done in a minute.

9
00:01:05,291 --> 00:01:06,916
Put your clothes on first.

10
00:01:09,000 --> 00:01:10,333
We're both guys.

11
00:01:10,625 --> 00:01:11,583
What are you scared of?

12
00:01:12,541 --> 00:01:13,833
You pervert.

13
00:01:17,291 --> 00:01:18,916
Hey, who you calling names?

14
00:01:20,541 --> 00:01:21,541
I can't be bothered to argue with you.

15
00:01:22,000 --> 00:01:23,583
The front desk must've messed up.

16
00:01:23,750 --> 00:01:24,458
I'm going to find her.

17
00:01:24,458 --> 00:01:26,500
Whoa whoa whoa, no no no.

18
00:01:26,875 --> 00:01:28,500
They didn't mess up. They didn't.

19
00:01:28,500 --> 00:01:30,000
I'm the one who messed up.

20
00:01:30,000 --> 00:01:31,166
This is your room.

21
00:01:31,583 --> 00:01:33,500
I'm leaving now. I'm leaving.

22
00:01:34,041 --> 00:01:35,000
Not good enough.

23
00:01:35,000 --> 00:01:36,666
This guesthouse is terribly run.

24
00:01:36,708 --> 00:01:37,333
I'm checking out.

25
00:01:37,333 --> 00:01:38,500
No no no no.

26
00:01:39,708 --> 00:01:41,833
Lijiang guesthouses are all like this.

27
00:01:42,208 --> 00:01:43,875
The service here is great.

28
00:01:43,916 --> 00:01:45,250
Stay a few days and you'll see.

29
00:01:45,333 --> 00:01:46,500
Service is great?

30
00:01:46,500 --> 00:01:47,125
Mm-hm.

31
00:01:47,125 --> 00:01:49,500
Then... what's all this?

32
00:01:50,875 --> 00:01:52,041
Uh, ha ha.

33
00:01:53,000 --> 00:01:54,083
This here, well...

34
00:01:54,083 --> 00:01:56,791
It was a tiny mistake.

35
00:01:56,791 --> 00:01:58,708
I didn't know you'd be here so soon.

36
00:01:59,000 --> 00:02:00,041
I'll fix it right now.

37
00:02:00,833 --> 00:02:01,666
Okay?

38
00:02:01,666 --> 00:02:03,000
Besides—

39
00:02:04,000 --> 00:02:06,916
I gave you a free show with this fine body of mine.

40
00:02:07,125 --> 00:02:08,500
Still not satisfied?

41
00:02:08,583 --> 00:02:10,375
Who wanted to see your body?

42
00:02:10,458 --> 00:02:11,583
I'm checking out.

43
00:02:12,416 --> 00:02:13,208
Hey.

44
00:02:16,666 --> 00:02:18,500
Why so worked up?

45
00:02:18,958 --> 00:02:20,625
Why—why are you getting so close to me?

46
00:02:20,625 --> 00:02:21,875
Are you harassing me?

47
00:02:26,333 --> 00:02:29,541
Har... ass... ment, huh?

48
00:02:31,208 --> 00:02:32,000
Like this?

49
00:02:33,833 --> 00:02:34,875
Hm?

50
00:02:34,875 --> 00:02:36,208
I'm calling the cops.

51
00:02:39,166 --> 00:02:40,000
The cops?

52
00:02:40,958 --> 00:02:43,083
Sure, go ahead. Call them.

53
00:02:44,208 --> 00:02:47,416
My uncle's the local beat cop around here.

54
00:02:48,750 --> 00:02:49,541
Call them.

55
00:02:50,250 --> 00:02:51,041
Go on, call.

56
00:02:52,750 --> 00:02:54,041
Then I'll file a complaint.

57
00:02:54,083 --> 00:02:55,208
I want to check out.

58
00:02:57,583 --> 00:02:59,708
Don't, I was kidding.

59
00:02:59,708 --> 00:03:00,875
Relax.

60
00:03:01,833 --> 00:03:03,291
I'm still checking out.

61
00:03:03,791 --> 00:03:05,541
Look at you.

62
00:03:06,291 --> 00:03:07,583
You just have to pick a fight.

63
00:03:08,083 --> 00:03:10,708
We've got no beef with each other.

64
00:03:10,750 --> 00:03:13,000
Can't we just talk it out?

65
00:03:13,000 --> 00:03:15,583
I'm leaving right now.

66
00:03:16,458 --> 00:03:17,291
Fine.

67
00:03:19,875 --> 00:03:23,250
Okay then... go on, hurry up and leave.

68
00:03:26,208 --> 00:03:28,041
All right, bye.

69
00:03:40,083 --> 00:03:42,583
Man, this guesthouse really is unreliable.

70
00:03:54,750 --> 00:03:56,291
Oh hell, this—

71
00:03:57,166 --> 00:03:58,833
What is this?

72
00:04:03,958 --> 00:04:05,250
Shady-ass guesthouse.

73
00:04:07,458 --> 00:04:08,250
Checking out.

74
00:04:09,000 --> 00:04:11,041
Ow ow ow, Mom, easy!

75
00:04:11,041 --> 00:04:12,000
It hurts, it hurts, it hurts.

76
00:04:12,000 --> 00:04:13,541
Ow, Mom, take it easy.

77
00:04:13,541 --> 00:04:14,166
Oh god, Mom.

78
00:04:14,166 --> 00:04:14,916
Ow.

79
00:04:15,041 --> 00:04:16,375
Hey there, handsome.

80
00:04:17,000 --> 00:04:18,291
See, this is my son.

81
00:04:18,291 --> 00:04:19,208
Ah.

82
00:04:19,833 --> 00:04:22,250
He, well, every time I'm not looking,

83
00:04:22,250 --> 00:04:23,916
he sneaks into empty rooms to paint.

84
00:04:23,916 --> 00:04:24,916
Today, somehow,

85
00:04:25,000 --> 00:04:27,791
he ended up in your room.

86
00:04:28,250 --> 00:04:29,583
I'm so sorry, so sorry.

87
00:04:29,583 --> 00:04:31,208
Apologize already, apologize!

88
00:04:31,916 --> 00:04:33,250
Um, hi, I—I'm Gao Ran.

89
00:04:33,250 --> 00:04:34,416
I'm Mosuo.

90
00:04:34,416 --> 00:04:35,791
The Mosuo? You know,

91
00:04:36,083 --> 00:04:37,541
the ones who do the midnight walking-marriage thing.

92
00:04:37,541 --> 00:04:38,208
Hey!

93
00:04:38,250 --> 00:04:40,333
What nonsense are you spewing?

94
00:04:40,333 --> 00:04:41,750
Ow, Mom, that hurts.

95
00:04:41,875 --> 00:04:42,833
Ow.

96
00:04:42,833 --> 00:04:44,250
I'm sorry, handsome.

97
00:04:44,250 --> 00:04:45,416
My son here,

98
00:04:45,416 --> 00:04:47,208
he studies art.

99
00:04:47,333 --> 00:04:49,041
His head, you see,

100
00:04:49,541 --> 00:04:50,958
is a little...

101
00:04:51,250 --> 00:04:51,708
Oh, oh.

102
00:04:51,708 --> 00:04:52,416
you know.

103
00:04:52,416 --> 00:04:53,041
Oh.

104
00:04:53,041 --> 00:04:55,416
Business is hard enough as it is,

105
00:04:56,208 --> 00:05:00,291
and the second he comes home for break, he's all over the place.

106
00:05:00,500 --> 00:05:02,750
Just making trouble for me, just making trouble.

107
00:05:02,958 --> 00:05:04,416
Just making trouble.

108
00:05:04,416 --> 00:05:05,250
Right, right.

109
00:05:08,458 --> 00:05:09,750
Tell you what,

110
00:05:09,750 --> 00:05:13,000
I'll knock a bit off your room rate,

111
00:05:13,000 --> 00:05:15,166
and throw in a basket of fruit.

112
00:05:15,166 --> 00:05:15,791
Oh.

113
00:05:15,791 --> 00:05:18,333
Yunnan fruit is delicious.

114
00:05:18,333 --> 00:05:19,208
Sweet, guaranteed.

115
00:05:19,208 --> 00:05:20,500
Oh, well...

116
00:05:20,958 --> 00:05:21,500
Okay then.

117
00:05:21,500 --> 00:05:24,833
Young man, you're so sweet.

118
00:05:25,166 --> 00:05:26,916
Ugh, not like you.

119
00:05:26,916 --> 00:05:29,041
Not like you, not like you.

120
00:05:30,041 --> 00:05:31,625
Always making trouble for me,

121
00:05:31,625 --> 00:05:33,625
trouble, trouble.

122
00:05:33,791 --> 00:05:34,291
Oh.

123
00:05:34,291 --> 00:05:35,250
Go, go, go.

124
00:05:35,333 --> 00:05:36,500
Go clean up.

125
00:05:36,500 --> 00:05:37,166
Okay, I'm heading out.

126
00:05:37,166 --> 00:05:39,416
Ow, Mom, easy!

127
00:05:40,125 --> 00:05:41,125
Ow.

128
00:06:11,375 --> 00:06:12,416
Chen,

129
00:06:12,625 --> 00:06:16,375
the Yunnan field-research data is part of your final grade,

130
00:06:16,500 --> 00:06:18,375
so do a good job with it.

131
00:06:18,875 --> 00:06:22,375
If you don't finish, it's fine to come back a few days late.

132
00:06:23,291 --> 00:06:25,958
Also, your professor here has to remind you—

133
00:06:26,000 --> 00:06:28,000
you young people love your fun.

134
00:06:28,000 --> 00:06:29,875
Going out for a bit is fine,

135
00:06:30,000 --> 00:06:32,708
but the work has to get done. Properly.

136
00:06:43,625 --> 00:06:44,666
Cleaning the room.

137
00:06:45,041 --> 00:06:46,458
Cleaning the room?

138
00:06:46,791 --> 00:06:47,750
Isn't that supposed to be in the morning?

139
00:06:47,750 --> 00:06:50,000
Our guesthouse isn't that strict.

140
00:06:50,083 --> 00:06:52,041
I clean whenever I have a free minute.

141
00:06:52,291 --> 00:06:55,583
And I painted in here this morning,

142
00:06:55,666 --> 00:06:58,458
so I figured I'd come change the sheets in case I got the bed dirty.

143
00:06:59,333 --> 00:07:01,000
Mom told me specifically

144
00:07:01,000 --> 00:07:03,166
to look out for you a little extra,

145
00:07:03,791 --> 00:07:05,500
to take good care of you.

146
00:07:06,125 --> 00:07:08,291
Consider it my apology.

147
00:07:08,458 --> 00:07:10,666
Whatever.

148
00:07:10,833 --> 00:07:12,125
You always have a story.

149
00:07:12,166 --> 00:07:13,000
Well then,

150
00:07:13,750 --> 00:07:14,791
get on with it.

151
00:07:28,375 --> 00:07:29,791
And about this reference—

152
00:07:29,833 --> 00:07:32,375
you cited Smith 2018,

153
00:07:32,500 --> 00:07:35,500
but Smith published a more recent one in 2020.

154
00:07:35,500 --> 00:07:36,666
Have you read it?

155
00:07:37,458 --> 00:07:40,458
Though the 2020 one ended up being pretty controversial.

156
00:07:40,875 --> 00:07:42,708
You might want to reconsider.

157
00:07:42,791 --> 00:07:44,166
And overall,

158
00:07:44,166 --> 00:07:46,458
his viewpoint has certain limitations.

159
00:07:46,583 --> 00:07:48,291
What I'm most afraid of is, after you cite him,

160
00:07:48,291 --> 00:07:51,000
you'll bring up unnecessary disputes or doubts.

161
00:07:51,000 --> 00:07:52,458
Then it's not worth the trouble.

162
00:07:54,000 --> 00:07:55,000
Hey, what are you doing?

163
00:07:55,000 --> 00:07:57,708
What a heavy gloomy aura.

164
00:07:59,000 --> 00:08:00,500
Can't bear it. Can't bear it.

165
00:08:00,916 --> 00:08:02,166
Turn it off, quick.

166
00:08:02,166 --> 00:08:03,666
I'm trying to work.

167
00:08:03,750 --> 00:08:05,833
What's the rush?

168
00:08:06,041 --> 00:08:07,916
You just checked in today.

169
00:08:08,750 --> 00:08:09,541
By the way—

170
00:08:09,875 --> 00:08:13,041
do you know what the soul of Lijiang is?

171
00:08:13,666 --> 00:08:14,625
What is it?

172
00:08:16,291 --> 00:08:18,000
Beautiful scenery, of course.

173
00:08:18,291 --> 00:08:19,750
And good liquor.

174
00:08:20,541 --> 00:08:21,375
Oh.

175
00:08:23,083 --> 00:08:24,291
Look at you.

176
00:08:24,541 --> 00:08:26,500
Working morning to night.

177
00:08:26,833 --> 00:08:28,333
Never going out for a stroll,

178
00:08:28,500 --> 00:08:30,208
to take in the scenery.

179
00:08:30,583 --> 00:08:32,041
Never having a drink.

180
00:08:32,208 --> 00:08:34,500
Just stewing in your own bad mood all day long.

181
00:08:35,416 --> 00:08:36,750
Is it worth it?

182
00:08:38,291 --> 00:08:40,541
Only the layabouts who don't have to work or study

183
00:08:40,541 --> 00:08:42,708
have time for scenery and liquor.

184
00:09:29,416 --> 00:09:30,333
Uh.

185
00:09:32,500 --> 00:09:33,875
Excuse me.

186
00:09:35,000 --> 00:09:37,583
Weren't you here to clean the room? Why are you lying down?

187
00:09:37,791 --> 00:09:39,833
There. All clean.

188
00:09:43,166 --> 00:09:46,500
Oh. Then... what are you doing?

189
00:09:46,958 --> 00:09:48,166
Painting again?

190
00:09:53,750 --> 00:09:55,458
Is that... me?

191
00:09:56,000 --> 00:09:57,416
Why are you painting me?

192
00:09:57,416 --> 00:09:58,583
Because—

193
00:10:00,083 --> 00:10:01,291
you're good-looking.

194
00:10:05,083 --> 00:10:06,541
Who said you could paint me?

195
00:10:06,708 --> 00:10:09,791
And besides, this is my room.

196
00:10:09,791 --> 00:10:11,541
Once you're done cleaning, you should leave.

197
00:10:13,041 --> 00:10:14,500
Here we go again.

198
00:10:15,791 --> 00:10:17,958
How can you be mad all day long?

199
00:10:19,250 --> 00:10:21,958
Lijiang is a place to relax.

200
00:10:22,416 --> 00:10:25,041
Did you take a wrong turn somewhere, dude?

201
00:10:26,916 --> 00:10:31,083
Okay, okay. I'll give you that one.

202
00:10:34,541 --> 00:10:35,500
How does it look?

203
00:10:35,666 --> 00:10:36,666
Let me see.

204
00:10:40,416 --> 00:10:41,708
Hm.

205
00:10:49,833 --> 00:10:50,875
Actually...

206
00:10:51,958 --> 00:10:53,333
it's pretty good.

207
00:10:56,583 --> 00:10:58,500
If you'd take your shirt off so I can paint you,

208
00:10:59,041 --> 00:11:00,500
it'd come out even better.

209
00:11:01,208 --> 00:11:02,791
Are you insane?

210
00:11:03,166 --> 00:11:04,916
It's art.

211
00:11:05,125 --> 00:11:06,916
Don't go getting any weird ideas.

212
00:11:08,291 --> 00:11:09,500
Who's getting weird ideas?

213
00:11:09,500 --> 00:11:11,000
Your mind's the dirty one.

214
00:11:11,000 --> 00:11:13,416
Fine, my mind's dirty.

215
00:11:14,583 --> 00:11:17,500
So could you please take your shirt off?

216
00:11:19,000 --> 00:11:19,833
You—

217
00:11:21,416 --> 00:11:22,500
Get away from me.

218
00:11:22,500 --> 00:11:24,000
Get away from me, I said.

219
00:11:24,000 --> 00:11:25,458
Are you harassing me again?

220
00:11:25,458 --> 00:11:27,125
I'm telling your mom.

221
00:11:28,125 --> 00:11:29,458
You sure you can stand to?

222
00:11:29,875 --> 00:11:31,625
Stand to my ass.

223
00:11:33,083 --> 00:11:35,125
Room's clean. Get out.

224
00:11:35,125 --> 00:11:36,416
Here we go again.

225
00:11:38,000 --> 00:11:40,250
Why do you blush so easily?

226
00:11:41,000 --> 00:11:42,625
Let me see.

227
00:11:43,375 --> 00:11:44,583
Now what?

228
00:11:44,625 --> 00:11:46,416
See your ass.

229
00:11:47,041 --> 00:11:50,791
Out, out, out, out.

230
00:11:52,708 --> 00:11:54,041
You're insane.

231
00:11:57,125 --> 00:11:57,958
Hey.

232
00:11:58,291 --> 00:12:00,083
You sure you won't let me draw you?

233
00:12:00,083 --> 00:12:01,541
I'll pay the model fee.

234
00:12:02,666 --> 00:12:04,875
Get out, get out.

235
00:12:04,916 --> 00:12:08,666
Out! Get out! You creep!

236
00:12:19,375 --> 00:12:21,375
Lijiang folks are wild, huh.

237
00:12:26,875 --> 00:12:27,875
Hey.

238
00:12:38,000 --> 00:12:38,875
Gao Ran.

239
00:12:39,791 --> 00:12:41,500
Gao Ran, come out for a drink.

240
00:12:41,500 --> 00:12:45,166
Coming! You guys are early.

241
00:12:45,666 --> 00:12:46,750
Right on time.

242
00:12:46,750 --> 00:12:47,958
Hurry up.

243
00:12:48,125 --> 00:12:50,000
Oh, everyone's here?

244
00:12:50,458 --> 00:12:51,791
You came too?

245
00:12:51,791 --> 00:12:53,375
Let's go, let's go.

246
00:12:54,625 --> 00:12:57,333
Ah, young people.

247
00:12:58,541 --> 00:13:00,208
So full of energy.

248
00:13:23,416 --> 00:13:24,208
Oh ho.

249
00:13:25,708 --> 00:13:27,250
White-Tee Lychee.

250
00:13:28,708 --> 00:13:30,125
What did you just say?

251
00:13:33,500 --> 00:13:36,083
Aww, all pale and tender.

252
00:13:37,000 --> 00:13:38,708
Just like a lychee.

253
00:13:47,541 --> 00:13:48,916
Beautiful once you peel it.

254
00:13:49,791 --> 00:13:50,750
And the taste—

255
00:13:55,125 --> 00:13:55,958
Mm.

256
00:13:56,708 --> 00:13:59,083
even more juicy.

257
00:13:59,416 --> 00:14:00,750
Don't talk crap.

258
00:14:02,000 --> 00:14:03,250
Hey, get away from me.

259
00:14:03,333 --> 00:14:04,250
You reek of liquor.

260
00:14:05,166 --> 00:14:06,000
Hey.

261
00:14:06,500 --> 00:14:08,041
What's your major anyway?

262
00:14:08,208 --> 00:14:10,083
Why's your schedule so old-fashioned?

263
00:14:11,208 --> 00:14:13,833
Lijiang's nightlife just hit its peak.

264
00:14:13,916 --> 00:14:17,666
Now is when young people are supposed to be sleeping.

265
00:14:17,791 --> 00:14:19,750
I study computer data engineering.

266
00:14:20,375 --> 00:14:22,166
It has nothing to do with my major.

267
00:14:22,250 --> 00:14:24,041
I just like going to bed early and getting up early.

268
00:14:26,083 --> 00:14:27,750
Coming all the way to Lijiang—

269
00:14:28,583 --> 00:14:32,125
and not going out for the nightlife or for drinks—

270
00:14:32,625 --> 00:14:34,041
isn't the trip wasted?

271
00:14:34,166 --> 00:14:36,541
I don't like that stuff. So what?

272
00:14:41,583 --> 00:14:43,375
Cute is cute.

273
00:14:43,833 --> 00:14:45,125
Just a little dim.

274
00:14:46,666 --> 00:14:47,458
Hey.

275
00:14:48,333 --> 00:14:49,666
I meant the lychee.

276
00:14:52,958 --> 00:14:54,083
Keep talking trash—

277
00:14:54,916 --> 00:14:56,208
and I'm filing a complaint.

278
00:14:56,333 --> 00:14:58,833
Hey, threatening me again.

279
00:14:59,541 --> 00:15:00,666
You win.

280
00:15:06,125 --> 00:15:06,958
Hey.

281
00:15:07,541 --> 00:15:09,208
That's my cup.

282
00:15:12,541 --> 00:15:13,416
Give it back.

283
00:15:17,791 --> 00:15:18,583
Hey.

284
00:15:23,500 --> 00:15:24,625
Petty.

285
00:15:25,833 --> 00:15:27,750
I just like your cup.

286
00:15:29,458 --> 00:15:31,083
I just figured—

